Dependencies
============

* screen
  * apt-get install screen

* sipp with authentication support
  * see `compiling sipp with authentication support`_

* argparse (if using python < 2.7)
  * apt-get install python-argparse

* jinja2
  * apt-get install python-jinja2


Compiling sipp with authentication support
------------------------------------------

1. Download the sipp stable release from http://sipp.sourceforge.net/doc/reference.html#Stable+release.
   This should be a file named "sipp.svn.tar.gz" in the latest 3.x directory.

2. Extract it::

      $ tar xvf sipp.svn.tar.gz
      $ cd sipp

3. Install the build dependencies::

      # apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev libncurses5-dev

4. Build it::

      $ make ossl

5. Install it::

      # cp sipp /usr/local/bin


Installation
============

To copy the project on trafgen, you can use the following command::

   rsync -v --exclude '*.pyc' --delete -rtlp * trafgen@trafgen:load-tester/
